I have been tagging along with my wife's guild with my SK for some time. They are a small guild who aren't capable of a whole lot due to low numbers and levels. So when they raid it's usually something small. They like to do what they can to help the guild out as a whole, so little mini raids to get people some &quot;ok&quot; gear in places like Umbral Planes is fun for them.<br>
<br>
So anyway, we are over there in umbral, and they are killing all the Shojens in hopes that a Raldukan pops(is that Breastplate really that rare? Or does it even exist? =P). Well as we are killing a couple of shojens, Dominatoor's crew appears in front of us. Not a second after we kill the last Shojen, I see Dominatoor stand up, invis, and go tearing off in to the zone. <br>
<br>
So as he is doing this, I warn their pullers of what I saw and what I know of Dominatoor and his ebay farm team. As this is going on, one by one his little farm team moves closer to the zone out. <br>
<br>
As the puller starts heading out, who should come racing in to the zone in area, but Dominatoor with the Raldukan right behind him. <br>
<br>
So far all of their effort,they got screwed by some ebay farming piece of garbage. When contacted he gave absolutely no response. That right there, shows he knows he was wrong, but doesn't give a shit. <br>
<br>
Now to most of you, the loot in umbral is inconsequential, but to this guild it helps them out greatly. To lose anything the Raldukan could have dropped hurt them quite a bit.<br>
<br>
It not only caused the puller to get pissed off so much that he logged, which evntually ruined the night of 20 other people who were there to help each other out. <br>
<br>
Now silly as it may sound, it's rather unfortunate, that some greedy, ebay pile of shit like him is able to continue his ways. <br>
I hope that the 10 bucks he got for the item is worth alienating 20+ people.<br>
